    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Outdoor game in which a ball, called a bowl, is rolled toward a smaller stationary ball, called a jack, the object being to roll one's bowl closer the jack than that of an opponent. This is sometimes achieved by knocking aside an opponent's bowl or the jack.</Note_Text>
